byline.original: By FALIH HASSAN and OMAR AL-JAWOSHY

abstract: Coordinated Islamic State suicide bombings kill at least 20 Iraqi soldiers and tribal fighters outside Ramadi and in Baghdad; bombings have increased as pro-government forces have made progress in retaking territory from militant group.
lead_paragraph: A day after the Islamic State staged a deadly wave of bombings in Baghdad, its forces struck Ramadi and the capital again.

headline.main: ISIS Kills Dozens in Iraq in New Round of Bombings
